WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.599 --> 00:00:17.226
Next time. maybe inform
the department chair

2
00:00:17.309 --> 00:00:18.268
before the shit hits the fan.

3
00:00:18.352 --> 00:00:19.937
I was on my way to tell you.

4
00:00:20.020 --> 00:00:21.271
Make sure you get
everything you need.

5
00:00:21.355 --> 00:00:22.356
OK. let's do this.

6
00:00:22.439 --> 00:00:23.941
IT called me up because

7
00:00:24.024 --> 00:00:26.276
I've trained in cyberattack
prevention and response.

8
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:27.569
Then you can tell everybody
what to do.

9
00:00:27.653 --> 00:00:28.946
No. thank you.

10
00:00:29.029 --> 00:00:30.197
Best if it comes
from the department chair.

11
00:00:30.280 --> 00:00:31.281
Oh. you think?

12
00:00:33.784 --> 00:00:35.953
All right. everybody.
circle up.

13
00:00:36.036 --> 00:00:37.204
What the fuck?

14
00:00:37.287 --> 00:00:39.164
We may have had
a cyberattack.

15
00:00:39.248 --> 00:00:41.500
No. we shut down
to prevent a cyberattack.

16
00:00:43.252 --> 00:00:45.254
OK. everybody. settle down.
Listen up.

17
00:00:45.337 --> 00:00:46.630
As you can see.
we're doing a little

18
00:00:46.713 --> 00:00:49.132
redecorating
in the central work area.

19
00:00:49.216 --> 00:00:52.010
Our hospital computers are
at risk for a cyberattack.

20
00:00:52.094 --> 00:00:54.012
so we are going old school.
analog.

21
00:00:54.096 --> 00:00:55.430
- For how long?
- Great question.

22
00:00:55.514 --> 00:00:57.474
Our IT department
has shut everything down

23
00:00:57.558 --> 00:00:59.810
to give them time to bolster
our cyber defenses.

24
00:00:59.893 --> 00:01:01.728
I believe the question was.
for how long?

25
00:01:01.812 --> 00:01:03.021
Uh. hard to say.

26
00:01:03.105 --> 00:01:04.313
Could be up to 24 hours.

27
00:01:04.397 --> 00:01:05.941
Jesus Christ.

28
00:01:06.024 --> 00:01:07.568
So first order of business.

29
00:01:07.651 --> 00:01:09.528
we need to replicate
the electronic patient boards

30
00:01:09.611 --> 00:01:10.862
on these dry-erase boards.

31
00:01:10.946 --> 00:01:11.947
So please. somebody tell me

32
00:01:12.030 --> 00:01:13.073
they got a photo of the boards.

33
00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:14.074
Uh. yeah. yeah. yeah.

34
00:01:14.157 --> 00:01:15.576
Right here. OK.

35
00:01:15.659 --> 00:01:16.702
Oh. uh...

36
00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:20.998
It's a little blurry.

37
00:01:21.081 --> 00:01:23.625
No. more than
a little blurry.

38
00:01:23.709 --> 00:01:26.420
- Sorry.
- Oh. my God.

39
00:01:26.503 --> 00:01:28.170
- I remember.
- Great.

40
00:01:28.255 --> 00:01:30.132
If everybody else can remember
their patient names

41
00:01:30.215 --> 00:01:31.508
and their room numbers.
that would be awesome.

42
00:01:31.592 --> 00:01:33.509
No. I mean
I can remember all of it.

43
00:01:33.594 --> 00:01:34.636
All of what?

44
00:01:34.720 --> 00:01:36.847
Names. doctors. room numbers.

45
00:01:36.930 --> 00:01:39.265
I kind of have
a photographic memory.

46
00:01:39.348 --> 00:01:41.393
Seriously? The whole board?

47
00:01:41.476 --> 00:01:43.770
Central 12.
Harlow Graham. headache.

48
00:01:43.854 --> 00:01:46.523
- abdominal pain. ASL only.
- Oh. shit.

49
00:01:46.607 --> 00:01:48.442
I have an interpreter
waiting for me.

50
00:01:48.525 --> 00:01:50.569
- Go.
- OK. for patient privacy.

51
00:01:50.652 --> 00:01:52.279
all chief complaints
will be abbreviated.

52
00:01:52.362 --> 00:01:53.614
So HA for headache.

53
00:01:53.697 --> 00:01:55.574
AP for abdominal pain.
and so forth.

54
00:01:55.657 --> 00:01:58.827
Central 10. Jackson Davis.
new-onset psychosis.

55
00:01:58.910 --> 00:02:00.287
Javadi. psych admission.

56
00:02:00.370 --> 00:02:02.289
Greek letter psi for psych.

57
00:02:02.372 --> 00:02:04.541
Pedes is Baby Jane Doe.
fever. Dr. Mohan.

58
00:02:04.625 --> 00:02:06.084
awaiting admission orders.

59
00:02:06.168 --> 00:02:07.794
Nurses need to convert
to a zone defense--

60
00:02:07.878 --> 00:02:08.836
north. central. south. trauma.

61
00:02:08.919 --> 00:02:10.005
Where's Dana?

62
00:02:10.088 --> 00:02:11.673
In with
a sexual assault case.

63
00:02:11.757 --> 00:02:13.258
She can't leave
until the exam is finished.

64
00:02:13.342 --> 00:02:14.551
Yeah. it could be a while.

65
00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:15.969
Princess has
charge nurse experience.

66
00:02:16.053 --> 00:02:17.429
- Not really.
- That's a great idea.

67
00:02:17.512 --> 00:02:18.680
Princess it is.

68
00:02:18.764 --> 00:02:19.681
You can make
the nursing assignments.

69
00:02:19.765 --> 00:02:21.016
- Next.
- Central 9.

70
00:02:21.099 --> 00:02:22.976
Roxie Hamler.
end-stage lung cancer.

71
00:02:23.060 --> 00:02:24.353
Sorry. do we have
to stand here while

72
00:02:24.436 --> 00:02:25.562
- she recites the whole board?
- No.

73
00:02:25.646 --> 00:02:26.813
In fact. go check
on your patients

74
00:02:26.897 --> 00:02:28.315
and then please come back here.

75
00:02:28.398 --> 00:02:29.858
Thank you.

76
00:02:29.941 --> 00:02:31.693
How many hours a day
are you on your laptop?

77
00:02:34.738 --> 00:02:35.989
At least eight hours.

78
00:02:36.073 --> 00:02:37.406
I work from home.

79
00:02:37.491 --> 00:02:39.368
And are you at a desk
all day?

80
00:02:41.244 --> 00:02:42.496
No. no.

81
00:02:42.579 --> 00:02:43.954
I will either sit on the sofa.

82
00:02:44.039 --> 00:02:46.208
or sometimes I'll be in bed.

83
00:02:46.291 --> 00:02:48.377
kind of sitting up
with the computer on my lap.

84
00:02:48.460 --> 00:02:49.920
that kind of thing.

85
00:02:50.003 --> 00:02:52.547
So you're always looking down
at the screen?

86
00:02:52.631 --> 00:02:54.174
- Yeah.
- OK.

87
00:02:54.257 --> 00:02:56.677
I'm going to check
the muscles in your neck.

88
00:03:03.392 --> 00:03:04.393
- Ooh!
- Ooh!

89
00:03:04.476 --> 00:03:06.603
Ow. that hurts.

90
00:03:06.687 --> 00:03:09.314
All right.
Well. I think we can help.

91
00:03:09.398 --> 00:03:11.483
Come on over.

92
00:03:11.566 --> 00:03:13.026
OK. gather up.

93
00:03:13.110 --> 00:03:15.237
Listen up. everybody.
This is our chart rack.

94
00:03:15.320 --> 00:03:17.197
So as you can see.
each slot and clipboard

95
00:03:17.280 --> 00:03:18.323
has a room number on it.

96
00:03:18.407 --> 00:03:19.741
When you pick up a new patient.

97
00:03:19.825 --> 00:03:22.119
you grab a fresh chart
from the T-system.

98
00:03:22.202 --> 00:03:25.122
Pick your chart
by chief complaint.

99
00:03:25.204 --> 00:03:27.332
Use the cartoon to find it.

100
00:03:27.416 --> 00:03:29.084
Why are there two bodies?

101
00:03:29.167 --> 00:03:31.086
Trauma on the left.
medical on the right.

102
00:03:31.169 --> 00:03:32.462
So head injury. you go left.

103
00:03:32.546 --> 00:03:34.005
Headache. go right.

104
00:03:34.089 --> 00:03:35.549
Are those fish
swimming in seaweed?

105
00:03:35.632 --> 00:03:36.633
No.

106
00:03:36.716 --> 00:03:37.968
That is bees and grass.

107
00:03:38.051 --> 00:03:39.219
That's the section
for insect bites.

108
00:03:39.302 --> 00:03:40.762
skin rash. allergies.

109
00:03:40.846 --> 00:03:42.347
OK. let's say. for example.

110
00:03:42.430 --> 00:03:44.474
Dr. Al-Hashimi has
a new patient with belly pain.

111
00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:47.102
For the history.
circle the positives.

112
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:49.062
like vomiting and diarrhea.

113
00:03:49.146 --> 00:03:51.690
Backslash the negative.
such as recent travel.

114
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.275
sick contacts. fever.

115
00:03:53.358 --> 00:03:57.195
For physical exam.
checkmark normals on the left.

116
00:03:57.279 --> 00:03:59.448
and circle any
abnormal findings on the right.

117
00:03:59.531 --> 00:04:00.532
Questions?

118
00:04:00.615 --> 00:04:01.742
Is your generative AI program

119
00:04:01.825 --> 00:04:02.743
still gonna be working?

120
00:04:04.202 --> 00:04:05.412
Not for a while.

121
00:04:05.495 --> 00:04:07.122
And ditch
your SpectraLink phones.

122
00:04:07.205 --> 00:04:08.749
Those are voice over internet.

123
00:04:11.835 --> 00:04:12.961
PTMC Emergency.

124
00:04:13.044 --> 00:04:14.504
Go ahead. Medic Command.

125
00:04:14.588 --> 00:04:15.672
That is how we will hear
about incoming runs.

126
00:04:15.756 --> 00:04:17.132
Thanks.

127
00:04:17.214 --> 00:04:18.841
Two minutes out with
abdominal pain and fever.

128
00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:20.302
OK. has everybody
got that so far?

129
00:04:20.385 --> 00:04:21.887
How do we write orders?

130
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:23.513
Physician order form
in triplicate.

131
00:04:23.597 --> 00:04:26.308
Labs. X-rays. IV fluid.
medication.

132
00:04:26.391 --> 00:04:27.726
Will the labs still be able
to run blood tests?

133
00:04:27.809 --> 00:04:29.102
Yes.

134
00:04:29.186 --> 00:04:30.520
Are the CT scanners
still working?

135
00:04:30.604 --> 00:04:31.855
Yes. but the results
will come back

136
00:04:31.938 --> 00:04:34.149
on paper from the radiologist.

137
00:04:34.232 --> 00:04:35.650
This is the dark ages.

138
00:04:35.734 --> 00:04:37.861
So if you have orders
with labs or X-rays.

139
00:04:37.944 --> 00:04:39.404
they go into
the clerk file here.

140
00:04:39.488 --> 00:04:40.697
They will sign them off.

141
00:04:40.781 --> 00:04:42.157
They will add
a downtime slip on them.

142
00:04:42.240 --> 00:04:43.450
make sure they go
to the correct department.

143
00:04:43.533 --> 00:04:44.993
I'm sorry.
who are the clerks?

144
00:04:45.076 --> 00:04:46.286
- You're looking at them.
- At your service.

145
00:04:46.369 --> 00:04:47.579
Larry and Antoine are
filling in

146
00:04:47.662 --> 00:04:49.122
- until more help arrives.
- We got this.

147
00:04:49.206 --> 00:04:51.207
After the clerk orders.
chart gets moved

148
00:04:51.291 --> 00:04:52.959
to the nursing order rack
here for IVs.

149
00:04:53.043 --> 00:04:54.711
medications. procedures.

150
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:56.922
Medications are locked up
in the PDS.

151
00:04:57.005 --> 00:04:59.716
The PDS is getting unlocked
by a clinical pharmacist.

152
00:04:59.800 --> 00:05:01.301
- Dr. Megan Nordt.
- We've got your back.

153
00:05:01.384 --> 00:05:02.302
This is a lot.

154
00:05:02.385 --> 00:05:04.262
Any questions? Yes.

155
00:05:04.346 --> 00:05:05.555
Uh. no.

156
00:05:05.639 --> 00:05:07.098
What's up
with the third rack?

157
00:05:07.182 --> 00:05:08.642
When your patient is
ready to be discharged.

158
00:05:08.725 --> 00:05:09.893
chart goes here.

159
00:05:09.976 --> 00:05:11.144
This lets everybody know

160
00:05:11.228 --> 00:05:12.395
we're about to have
an open bed.

161
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:14.189
Or that your tuna melt is up.

162
00:05:14.272 --> 00:05:15.524
Jesse?

163
00:05:16.817 --> 00:05:18.777
- What is that?
- What is that?

164
00:05:18.860 --> 00:05:20.570
That is a fax machine.

165
00:05:20.654 --> 00:05:22.030
They still make those?

166
00:05:22.113 --> 00:05:23.865
This is our lifeline
to labs and X-rays.

167
00:05:23.949 --> 00:05:25.742
When the results come back.
they will fax to us.

168
00:05:25.826 --> 00:05:27.452
and the clerks will
put them on the charts.

169
00:05:27.536 --> 00:05:28.787
- Yes?
- If you say so.

170
00:05:28.870 --> 00:05:30.539
Incoming.

171
00:05:30.622 --> 00:05:33.792
OK. Dr. McKay. Dr. Whitaker.
Ogilvie. you're with me.

172
00:05:33.875 --> 00:05:36.628
The rest of you.
build your clipboards.

173
00:05:39.005 --> 00:05:41.633
Howard Knox. 52.
abdominal pain and fever.

174
00:05:41.716 --> 00:05:44.302
152 over 90. tachy at 120.

175
00:05:44.386 --> 00:05:46.054
- Couldn't get an IV.
- I wonder why.

176
00:05:46.137 --> 00:05:47.639
Hello. sir.
My name is Dr. Robby.

177
00:05:47.722 --> 00:05:50.058
- Howard.
- This is a teaching hospital.

178
00:05:50.141 --> 00:05:52.185
I'll be supervising
Doctors McKay and Dr. Whitaker

179
00:05:52.269 --> 00:05:53.436
- and student Dr. Ogilvie.
- Hey.

180
00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:54.604
- Hello.
- How are you feeling?

181
00:05:54.688 --> 00:05:56.022
- Not so great.
- OK.

182
00:05:56.106 --> 00:05:57.524
- Princess. what's free?
- Trauma 1.

183
00:05:57.607 --> 00:05:58.942
Perlah?

184
00:06:01.403 --> 00:06:04.948
All right. orders for Mylanta
and bupivacaine. Central 12.

185
00:06:05.031 --> 00:06:06.324
Wrong spot. Dr. Santos.

186
00:06:06.408 --> 00:06:08.326
And you need a sticker.

187
00:06:10.078 --> 00:06:11.329
Put it
in the nursing orders rack.

188
00:06:11.413 --> 00:06:12.831
And meet me over at PDS.

189
00:06:12.914 --> 00:06:14.416
How much does this suck?

190
00:06:14.499 --> 00:06:16.126
I didn't think
today could get any worse.

191
00:06:16.209 --> 00:06:18.253
This is how we rolled
when I was a resident.

192
00:06:18.336 --> 00:06:19.838
Was that in the 1900s?

193
00:06:19.921 --> 00:06:22.132
Yeah. when charts were
written by candlelight.

194
00:06:22.215 --> 00:06:23.967
Hey. today will be
an adventure.

195
00:06:24.050 --> 00:06:26.261
Think of it like
"Back to the Future."

196
00:06:28.889 --> 00:06:30.849
Or possibly "Titanic."

197
00:06:30.932 --> 00:06:32.726
Here is your antacid.

198
00:06:32.808 --> 00:06:34.102
Cheers.

199
00:06:34.185 --> 00:06:35.854
And I marked the trigger point

200
00:06:35.937 --> 00:06:37.397
that is bringing out
your headache.

201
00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:39.149
and a shot of local anesthetic
in that area

202
00:06:39.232 --> 00:06:41.192
could really help.

203
00:06:42.444 --> 00:06:43.445
Yeah. let's do it.

204
00:06:43.528 --> 00:06:44.738
All right.

205
00:06:45.947 --> 00:06:48.658
You are going to feel
a little pinprick

206
00:06:48.742 --> 00:06:50.327
and some burning.

207
00:06:55.999 --> 00:06:57.876
OK.

208
00:06:57.959 --> 00:06:59.878
Oh. ow. ow.
that really hurts.

209
00:06:59.961 --> 00:07:04.382
Temp 101.4. tachy at 128.
pulse ox 92 on 2 liters.

210
00:07:04.466 --> 00:07:05.759
When did the pain start?

211
00:07:05.842 --> 00:07:07.302
It's been on and off
for about a week.

212
00:07:07.385 --> 00:07:09.095
- And where do you feel it?
- All over.

213
00:07:09.179 --> 00:07:11.640
It started on the left. and now
there's some on the right.

214
00:07:11.723 --> 00:07:12.849
How about that fever?

215
00:07:12.933 --> 00:07:14.184
Since last night.

216
00:07:14.267 --> 00:07:15.560
I was burning up.

217
00:07:15.644 --> 00:07:17.395
Then I had chills pretty bad.

218
00:07:17.479 --> 00:07:18.396
I can't find a vein here.

219
00:07:18.480 --> 00:07:19.439
We'll try for a midline.

220
00:07:19.522 --> 00:07:21.191
Let us know if this hurts.

221
00:07:21.274 --> 00:07:22.567
- Ah. ah.
- Sorry.

222
00:07:22.651 --> 00:07:24.444
- And on this side?
- Yeah. yeah!

223
00:07:24.527 --> 00:07:25.570
Sorry. sir.

224
00:07:25.654 --> 00:07:26.655
Guarding with no rigidity.

225
00:07:26.738 --> 00:07:28.823
For pain. 100 of fent IM?

226
00:07:28.907 --> 00:07:30.158
Plan. Dr. Whitaker?

227
00:07:30.241 --> 00:07:32.869
Blood cultures.
lactate. Zosyn.

228
00:07:32.953 --> 00:07:35.372
We're gonna need a CT
to figure out what's going on.

229
00:07:35.455 --> 00:07:36.790
Ah-ah.

230
00:07:36.873 --> 00:07:38.832
- Yeah. it's not gonna work.
- Yep.

231
00:07:38.917 --> 00:07:40.168
Write neatly.
Penmanship counts.

232
00:07:40.251 --> 00:07:41.503
Howard. for the scan.
we're gonna have

233
00:07:41.586 --> 00:07:42.587
to lay you flat on your back.

234
00:07:42.671 --> 00:07:43.838
Can you do that?

235
00:07:43.922 --> 00:07:45.090
I could ten years ago.

236
00:07:45.173 --> 00:07:46.675
but now
it's too hard to breathe.

237
00:07:46.758 --> 00:07:48.385
If we can't lay you flat.

238
00:07:48.468 --> 00:07:49.886
then we're gonna have to put
a tube in your windpipe

239
00:07:49.970 --> 00:07:51.388
to help you breathe--
are you OK with that?

240
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:52.889
Intubation with rapid
sequence induction?

241
00:07:52.973 --> 00:07:54.224
No. we can't lay him down.

242
00:07:54.307 --> 00:07:55.392
The tube will go in your nose

243
00:07:55.475 --> 00:07:56.518
while you're awake. sir.

244
00:07:56.601 --> 00:07:57.560
- Well...
- Right.

245
00:07:57.644 --> 00:07:58.853
Does it hurt?

246
00:07:58.937 --> 00:08:00.021
You'll be numbed up
completely.

247
00:08:00.105 --> 00:08:01.439
You won't feel any discomfort.

248
00:08:01.523 --> 00:08:04.317
Do you happen
to know your weight?

249
00:08:04.401 --> 00:08:05.986
A little over 400.

250
00:08:06.069 --> 00:08:07.320
When was the last time
you checked?

251
00:08:07.404 --> 00:08:08.822
It's been a while.

252
00:08:08.905 --> 00:08:11.282
Is it possible
that you might be over 450?

253
00:08:11.366 --> 00:08:13.243
Possibly.

254
00:08:13.326 --> 00:08:15.537
Perlah.
let's call for the Hoyer.

255
00:08:15.620 --> 00:08:18.540
So we're gonna place the tube
and get you ready for the scan.

256
00:08:18.623 --> 00:08:20.207
Is this something serious?

257
00:08:20.291 --> 00:08:22.002
Well. it's hard to tell
without a CT.

258
00:08:22.085 --> 00:08:23.712
You could just need
antibiotics.

259
00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:25.505
or you could require
an operation.

260
00:08:25.588 --> 00:08:26.798
If surgery is necessary.

261
00:08:26.881 --> 00:08:28.133
then your weight could
make things

262
00:08:28.216 --> 00:08:29.551
- a little bit more complicated.
- I know.

263
00:08:29.634 --> 00:08:31.136
- I'm sorry.
- Not to worry.

264
00:08:31.219 --> 00:08:32.554
We're gonna take
very good care of you.

265
00:08:32.636 --> 00:08:33.847
Team.

266
00:08:33.929 --> 00:08:34.972
OK.

267
00:08:35.056 --> 00:08:36.474
Pain medication for you. OK?

268
00:08:36.558 --> 00:08:38.351
Let's try for a midline.

269
00:08:38.434 --> 00:08:40.227
basilic vein
with ultrasound guidance.

270
00:08:40.311 --> 00:08:41.688
Can ultrasound check
for an appy?

271
00:08:41.770 --> 00:08:43.565
He's a little too large
for an ultrasound.

272
00:08:43.648 --> 00:08:45.984
Plus. our CT can only handle
450 pounds.

273
00:08:46.067 --> 00:08:48.528
And so if he's over that.
we send him to the zoo?

274
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:50.905
He's right there.

275
00:08:53.241 --> 00:08:56.202
I--I heard that there's
a large animal CT at the zoo.

276
00:08:56.286 --> 00:08:58.204
Presby's CT can handle 650.

277
00:08:58.288 --> 00:09:00.415
Yeah. if Presby's still
up and running.

278
00:09:00.498 --> 00:09:01.916
Wh...

279
00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:03.918
That--that's not a jinx.
It's--

280
00:09:04.002 --> 00:09:06.546
Have any of you ever done
an awake naso-tracheal?

281
00:09:06.629 --> 00:09:07.839
OK.

282
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:08.923
Perlah. can you also ask

283
00:09:09.007 --> 00:09:10.091
Dr. Al-Hashimi to come in?

284
00:09:10.175 --> 00:09:11.176
I'm gonna need an assist.

285
00:09:11.259 --> 00:09:12.552
Yep. You got it.

286
00:09:12.635 --> 00:09:14.596
Ah. sorry. Signed.

287
00:09:15.764 --> 00:09:18.933
Hall bed F. George Francis.
shortness of breath.

288
00:09:19.017 --> 00:09:21.394
Dr. Mohan. awaiting D-dimer.

289
00:09:21.478 --> 00:09:23.021
Wow. She's still going?

290
00:09:23.104 --> 00:09:25.148
Yeah. Remarkable. really.

291
00:09:25.231 --> 00:09:26.733
Dr. Al.
Robby's asking for you.

292
00:09:26.816 --> 00:09:27.942
Uh. OK.

293
00:09:28.026 --> 00:09:29.694
In Trauma if you need me.
Princess.

294
00:09:29.778 --> 00:09:30.904
Got it.

295
00:09:32.530 --> 00:09:34.032
Who's supposed to run
the downtime slips

296
00:09:34.115 --> 00:09:35.241
to X-ray and lab?

297
00:09:35.325 --> 00:09:37.744
Uh. the charge nurse?

298
00:09:37.827 --> 00:09:39.537
Don't look at me.

299
00:09:39.621 --> 00:09:40.997
My plate's full!

300
00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:45.627
Uh. parents of Roxie Hamler?

301
00:09:45.710 --> 00:09:46.878
Central 9.

302
00:09:46.961 --> 00:09:48.171
Oh. I got it. Donnie.

303
00:09:48.254 --> 00:09:49.464
Hi. I'm Victoria Javadi.

304
00:09:49.547 --> 00:09:50.924
one of the student
doctors here.

305
00:09:51.007 --> 00:09:52.467
I've been assisting
with Roxie's care.

306
00:09:52.550 --> 00:09:53.843
Oh. thank you so much.

307
00:09:53.927 --> 00:09:56.054
- I'm Lloyd.
- Cora.

308
00:09:56.137 --> 00:09:57.180
It's nice to meet you.

309
00:09:57.263 --> 00:09:58.348
She broke her leg?

310
00:09:58.431 --> 00:09:59.682
Um. yeah.

311
00:09:59.766 --> 00:10:01.434
There's a fracture
down by the ankle.

312
00:10:01.518 --> 00:10:03.978
She's in a boot now. so there's
not quite so much pain.

313
00:10:04.062 --> 00:10:06.356
But I'll take you.
She's just in 9.

314
00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:13.154
The hospital Wi-Fi
isn't working.

315
00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:14.531
Oh. it'll be down
for a while.

316
00:10:14.614 --> 00:10:16.366
Sorry.

317
00:10:16.449 --> 00:10:18.868
Mom broke her leg. Grandpa.

318
00:10:18.952 --> 00:10:20.995
We heard.

319
00:10:21.079 --> 00:10:22.705
How are you. honey?

320
00:10:24.958 --> 00:10:27.293
You've got this. kiddo.

321
00:10:27.377 --> 00:10:29.587
Yeah.

322
00:10:29.671 --> 00:10:31.673
How long will she stay
in the ER?

323
00:10:31.756 --> 00:10:35.301
Oh. until a bed
opens up upstairs.

324
00:10:35.385 --> 00:10:36.928
Could be a while.

325
00:10:42.225 --> 00:10:43.893
You know. it's getting
pretty crowded in here.

326
00:10:43.977 --> 00:10:45.645
Maybe we should take Tucker
and Shane out for ice cream.

327
00:10:45.728 --> 00:10:49.107
- Yes. please.
- No. no. I'm OK.

328
00:10:49.190 --> 00:10:52.277
Maybe your mom would like
some time to rest.

329
00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.487
Yeah. Go.

330
00:10:56.197 --> 00:10:58.533
Can she have ice cream?

331
00:10:58.616 --> 00:11:01.744
She can have
anything she wants.

332
00:11:01.828 --> 00:11:04.706
Come on. let's go.

333
00:11:04.789 --> 00:11:06.624
Bye. Mom.

334
00:11:08.334 --> 00:11:10.545
Ice cream. ice cream.

335
00:11:13.840 --> 00:11:15.133
Yep.

336
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:17.135
Listen up.

337
00:11:17.218 --> 00:11:18.636
This is Oxymetazoline.

338
00:11:18.720 --> 00:11:19.637
This will open up the passage.

339
00:11:20.889 --> 00:11:22.265
What medication do you take?

340
00:11:22.348 --> 00:11:25.059
Uh. Lisinopril and Metformin.

341
00:11:25.143 --> 00:11:26.978
Ozempic? Wegovy?

342
00:11:27.061 --> 00:11:28.897
No. Kind of expensive.

343
00:11:28.980 --> 00:11:30.857
I'm going to squirt
some numbing gel in your nose.

344
00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:34.360
If it drips back
in your throat. that's OK.

345
00:11:34.444 --> 00:11:36.654
Here. in case you need it.

346
00:11:36.738 --> 00:11:38.489
Do you smoke?

347
00:11:38.573 --> 00:11:39.782
Alcohol?

348
00:11:39.866 --> 00:11:41.868
- Never.
- Do you exercise?

349
00:11:41.951 --> 00:11:44.329
Moving from the bedroom
to the kitchen.

350
00:11:44.412 --> 00:11:45.830
No. I'd walk more.

351
00:11:45.914 --> 00:11:48.458
but I need a bench
to rest on every block.

352
00:11:48.540 --> 00:11:49.959
What about water aerobics?

353
00:11:50.043 --> 00:11:52.253
Let's focus
on helping Mr. Knox.

354
00:11:52.337 --> 00:11:53.671
Agreed.

355
00:11:53.755 --> 00:11:55.673
It took me 25 years
to get this way.

356
00:11:55.757 --> 00:11:58.301
Car crash. burn unit.

357
00:11:58.384 --> 00:12:01.095
four leg surgeries
over ten years.

358
00:12:01.179 --> 00:12:03.306
Laid me up so much.
I lost my job.

359
00:12:03.389 --> 00:12:04.974
I need to numb
the back of your tongue.

360
00:12:05.058 --> 00:12:06.809
This is gonna taste pretty bad.

361
00:12:06.893 --> 00:12:08.228
Is there anyone
you'd like us to call?

362
00:12:08.311 --> 00:12:09.395
No.

363
00:12:09.479 --> 00:12:10.939
Any family?

364
00:12:11.022 --> 00:12:13.524
Mm. My parents passed.

365
00:12:13.608 --> 00:12:14.734
I'm single.

366
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:15.735
Go figure.

367
00:12:15.818 --> 00:12:16.945
Siblings?

368
00:12:17.028 --> 00:12:18.947
Sister in Arizona.

369
00:12:19.030 --> 00:12:21.366
We don't talk much.

370
00:12:21.449 --> 00:12:23.243
Now that we've numbed up
the back of your tongue.

371
00:12:23.326 --> 00:12:26.788
we can anesthetize
a bit deeper.

372
00:12:26.871 --> 00:12:27.789
Um. sorry to interrupt.

373
00:12:27.872 --> 00:12:28.790
I have a middle-aged woman

374
00:12:28.873 --> 00:12:30.458
with sudden onset blindness.

375
00:12:30.541 --> 00:12:31.834
- I can go.
- OK.

376
00:12:31.918 --> 00:12:33.086
Will you see if Abbot's
still around?

377
00:12:33.169 --> 00:12:34.087
- Yeah.
- Thank you.

378
00:12:34.170 --> 00:12:35.713
What's your sister's name?

379
00:12:35.797 --> 00:12:37.423
Lauren Milford.

380
00:12:37.507 --> 00:12:38.925
Where in Arizona?

381
00:12:39.008 --> 00:12:40.551
Flagstaff. I think.

382
00:12:40.635 --> 00:12:41.761
Just gonna go
over your tongue

383
00:12:41.844 --> 00:12:42.971
and numb your vocal cords.

384
00:12:43.054 --> 00:12:43.972
Ah.

385
00:12:44.055 --> 00:12:46.349
Ah...

386
00:12:46.432 --> 00:12:47.517
How many fingers?

387
00:12:47.600 --> 00:12:49.727
I don't see any fingers.

388
00:12:49.811 --> 00:12:51.688
And now?

389
00:12:51.771 --> 00:12:54.232
I can see a little bit
of light.

390
00:12:54.315 --> 00:12:55.984
Um. Brooke.
you've met Dr. King.

391
00:12:56.067 --> 00:12:57.485
This is Dr. Al-Hashimi.

392
00:12:57.568 --> 00:12:58.820
- Nice to meet you.
- And her wife. Wendy.

393
00:12:58.903 --> 00:13:00.113
- Hello.
- Hello.

394
00:13:00.196 --> 00:13:01.864
OK if we discuss
your symptoms?

395
00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:04.075
As long as I can correct you
if you get anything wrong.

396
00:13:04.158 --> 00:13:05.868
Trust me. she will.

397
00:13:05.952 --> 00:13:08.955
One hour of sudden. painless
vision loss in the left eye.

398
00:13:09.038 --> 00:13:10.790
No history
of hypercoagulable state

399
00:13:10.873 --> 00:13:12.166
or vascular disease.

400
00:13:12.250 --> 00:13:13.710
Could you look straight ahead.
please?

401
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:16.170
Could be a central
retinal artery occlusion.

402
00:13:16.254 --> 00:13:17.630
In English. please?

403
00:13:17.714 --> 00:13:19.799
A little blood clot
can block the artery

404
00:13:19.882 --> 00:13:22.385
at the back of the eye
and decrease your vision.

405
00:13:22.468 --> 00:13:24.012
Sometimes it's called
an eye stroke.

406
00:13:24.095 --> 00:13:25.013
Stroke?

407
00:13:25.096 --> 00:13:26.431
Like she could be paralyzed?

408
00:13:26.514 --> 00:13:27.974
No. this would be
limited to the eye.

409
00:13:28.057 --> 00:13:29.392
Is it permanent?

410
00:13:29.475 --> 00:13:31.769
First. we have
to make the diagnosis.

411
00:13:31.853 --> 00:13:32.979
Retinal exam?

412
00:13:33.062 --> 00:13:34.022
Hard to get a good look.

413
00:13:34.105 --> 00:13:35.606
We need the FOP.

414
00:13:35.690 --> 00:13:37.358
The what?

415
00:13:39.736 --> 00:13:41.404
Oh. Princess.

416
00:13:41.487 --> 00:13:43.364
We need patient stickers
on each of these order sheets.

417
00:13:43.448 --> 00:13:45.491
or the pharmacy won't know
who to give meds to.

418
00:13:45.575 --> 00:13:46.909
We're on it.

419
00:13:46.993 --> 00:13:49.078
Princess.
smartphone fundoscope?

420
00:13:49.162 --> 00:13:50.455
Equipment corridor. eye cart.

421
00:13:50.538 --> 00:13:53.583
- Thanks.
- You seem a little confused.

422
00:13:53.665 --> 00:13:55.376
How do I figure out
which new patient to pick up?

423
00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:56.711
Top of the board.

424
00:13:56.794 --> 00:13:57.920
They're listed
in the order they arrive.

425
00:13:58.004 --> 00:13:59.172
You erase the first one.
then put

426
00:13:59.255 --> 00:14:00.631
your initials in the MD box.

427
00:14:00.715 --> 00:14:02.258
OK. Thanks.

428
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:03.634
- Caleb.
- Michael.

429
00:14:03.718 --> 00:14:05.470
Are you managing this chaos OK?

430
00:14:05.553 --> 00:14:08.097
Well. it's all pretty easy
when you're a short-timer.

431
00:14:08.181 --> 00:14:10.725
Any more comatose patients
for me to have a chat with?

432
00:14:12.518 --> 00:14:13.770
I'm kidding.

433
00:14:13.853 --> 00:14:15.355
OK.

434
00:14:15.438 --> 00:14:17.023
Victoria.
this is Nicole Steadman.

435
00:14:17.106 --> 00:14:18.232
I run
the parent support group

436
00:14:18.316 --> 00:14:19.692
for the psychiatric service.

437
00:14:19.776 --> 00:14:21.486
Yeah.
Nicole's daughter was diagnosed

438
00:14:21.569 --> 00:14:23.237
sophomore year in college.

439
00:14:23.321 --> 00:14:26.366
You think Jackson's parents
might have a chat with her?

440
00:14:26.449 --> 00:14:28.284
We can certainly ask.

441
00:14:28.368 --> 00:14:29.952
Now we can see
the whole retina

442
00:14:30.036 --> 00:14:31.454
without dilating the pupil.

443
00:14:32.663 --> 00:14:34.207
You're looking
in the wrong eye.

444
00:14:34.290 --> 00:14:36.459
Oh. we start with
the good eye for comparison.

445
00:14:36.542 --> 00:14:38.544
Oh.

446
00:14:38.628 --> 00:14:39.629
Retina looks great.

447
00:14:39.712 --> 00:14:40.797
Now for the bad eye?

448
00:14:40.880 --> 00:14:42.131
Eyes wide open.

449
00:14:44.592 --> 00:14:45.885
How's it look?

450
00:14:45.968 --> 00:14:47.470
Extremely pale.
no blood flow.

451
00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:49.597
Digital massage.
10 seconds on. 5 seconds off.

452
00:14:49.680 --> 00:14:53.059
Order non-contrast head CT.

453
00:14:54.685 --> 00:14:56.729
Come in.

454
00:14:56.813 --> 00:14:57.897
Hi.

455
00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.315
Heard your patient took off.

456
00:14:59.399 --> 00:15:00.858
She's taking a little break.

457
00:15:00.942 --> 00:15:03.236
How long are you gonna wait?

458
00:15:03.319 --> 00:15:05.113
You know about
the cyber shutdown thing?

459
00:15:05.196 --> 00:15:06.656
Yeah.

460
00:15:06.739 --> 00:15:08.116
Wish I could help.
but I gotta stay here

461
00:15:08.199 --> 00:15:09.534
till all the evidence
is collected. so...

462
00:15:09.617 --> 00:15:11.160
It's a hot mess out there.

463
00:15:11.244 --> 00:15:12.537
This whole day is.

464
00:15:13.704 --> 00:15:16.165
Sorry.
I was just leaving.

465
00:15:16.249 --> 00:15:18.334
You OK?

466
00:15:18.418 --> 00:15:19.794
I'm good.

467
00:15:19.877 --> 00:15:21.546
I'm glad to hear it.

468
00:15:21.629 --> 00:15:22.588
You get something to eat?

469
00:15:22.672 --> 00:15:25.466
No.

470
00:15:25.550 --> 00:15:27.593
Let's keep going.

471
00:15:27.677 --> 00:15:28.928
OK.

472
00:15:29.011 --> 00:15:30.054
Yeah.

473
00:15:40.523 --> 00:15:42.942
Why don't we keep one
in the ER?

474
00:15:43.025 --> 00:15:46.612
Because our intubated
patients are usually sedated.

475
00:15:46.696 --> 00:15:48.114
Right.

476
00:15:48.197 --> 00:15:49.740
Maybe you could ease up

477
00:15:49.824 --> 00:15:51.409
with your comments
about his weight.

478
00:15:52.869 --> 00:15:54.745
I was just wondering
how he got so big

479
00:15:54.829 --> 00:15:56.414
and how we could help.

480
00:15:56.497 --> 00:15:58.124
We can help by finding out
what's wrong with him

481
00:15:58.207 --> 00:15:59.167
and treating him with respect.

482
00:15:59.250 --> 00:16:00.168
How's your belly now?

483
00:16:00.251 --> 00:16:01.502
Second pain shot helped.

484
00:16:01.586 --> 00:16:03.379
OK.
There's more if you need it.

485
00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:04.630
Diminished bowel sounds.

486
00:16:04.714 --> 00:16:05.965
VidaTalk from the ICU.

487
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:07.550
Great.

488
00:16:07.633 --> 00:16:08.843
Howard. we need to open up
that passageway now

489
00:16:08.926 --> 00:16:10.094
so we can pass the tube.

490
00:16:10.178 --> 00:16:11.679
I'm gonna start
with my pinky.

491
00:16:11.762 --> 00:16:13.097
Slowly. over a few minutes.
I'm gonna go deeper.

492
00:16:13.181 --> 00:16:14.557
all the way to the back
of my knuckle.

493
00:16:14.640 --> 00:16:16.267
Once the tube's
through your vocal cords.

494
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:17.768
you won't be able to talk.

495
00:16:17.852 --> 00:16:19.520
But this is
a communication device.

496
00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:22.190
Swipe through the screen
for anything you want to say.

497
00:16:22.273 --> 00:16:24.692
Hit the icon.
and it talks to us.

498
00:16:24.775 --> 00:16:26.944
I would like
some pain medicine.

499
00:16:27.028 --> 00:16:28.779
My pain is a nine.

500
00:16:28.863 --> 00:16:30.448
Can I get it
to order a pizza?

501
00:16:32.909 --> 00:16:34.660
There's cell service
in the ambulance bay.

502
00:16:34.744 --> 00:16:37.205
I found his sister's
new number. left a voicemail.

503
00:16:37.288 --> 00:16:38.456
OK. I'm gonna start.

504
00:16:38.539 --> 00:16:39.665
You ready?

505
00:16:39.749 --> 00:16:41.125
Not really.

506
00:16:41.209 --> 00:16:42.126
Go ahead.

507
00:16:42.210 --> 00:16:43.503
Robby. over here.

508
00:16:43.586 --> 00:16:45.796
Here we go. Head back.

509
00:16:47.256 --> 00:16:48.466
You thinking it's surgical?

510
00:16:48.549 --> 00:16:49.926
I'm hoping
for a non-perfed appy.

511
00:16:50.009 --> 00:16:51.511
- Can you do it with a scope?
- Possibly.

512
00:16:51.594 --> 00:16:53.179
but he could be treated
with antibiotics alone.

513
00:16:53.262 --> 00:16:55.181
And if he needs surgery?

514
00:16:55.264 --> 00:16:58.184
With his size.
an emergency open laparotomy.

515
00:16:58.267 --> 00:17:00.311
death rate's close to 50%.

516
00:17:00.394 --> 00:17:01.896
OK. one step at a time.

517
00:17:01.979 --> 00:17:04.482
Let's keep trying his sister
every 15 minutes.

518
00:17:04.565 --> 00:17:05.900
She'll get it.

519
00:17:09.819 --> 00:17:12.906
Half the downtime slips
are blank.

520
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.992
What are you talking about?

521
00:17:15.076 --> 00:17:17.161
Here and here.

522
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:19.247
Larry. are you using
a felt tip pen?

523
00:17:19.329 --> 00:17:21.540
Maybe.

524
00:17:21.624 --> 00:17:24.835
It's not going through
for the copies.

525
00:17:24.919 --> 00:17:26.628
Ballpoint pen only.

526
00:17:26.712 --> 00:17:28.047
OK.

527
00:17:30.508 --> 00:17:31.801
Digby still MIA?

528
00:17:31.884 --> 00:17:33.010
Is that the homeless guy?

529
00:17:33.094 --> 00:17:34.845
We need the bed if he eloped.

