And my deposition's coming up.

796
00:28:33.212 --> 00:28:35.631
Think of this as a great way
to steal some quiet time

797
00:28:35.714 --> 00:28:36.924
and get mentally prepared.

798
00:28:37.007 --> 00:28:39.218
Jesse. Mel's with you.

799
00:28:41.011 --> 00:28:42.930
Oh. excuse me. Dr. Mohan.

800
00:28:43.013 --> 00:28:44.056
Excuse me.

801
00:28:44.139 --> 00:28:45.057
Dr. Mohan.

802
00:28:45.140 --> 00:28:46.475
Uh. in a minute. George.

803
00:28:46.558 --> 00:28:47.559
I've got this.

804
00:28:47.643 --> 00:28:48.769
Thank you.

805
00:28:48.852 --> 00:28:51.104
Oh. uh. I. um--

806
00:28:51.188 --> 00:28:53.273
D-dimer is back normal.

807
00:28:53.357 --> 00:28:54.274
Oh.

808
00:28:54.358 --> 00:28:55.609
I'm ready to go.

809
00:28:55.692 --> 00:28:57.486
Are you feeling better?

810
00:28:57.569 --> 00:29:01.240
I--I really wasn't
short of breath this time.

811
00:29:02.407 --> 00:29:04.034
Then why'd you come in?

812
00:29:05.619 --> 00:29:07.579
When I found out about
the blood clot in my leg.

813
00:29:07.663 --> 00:29:10.499
I just kept thinking it's gonna
go to my lung and kill me.

814
00:29:10.582 --> 00:29:13.669
We've talked before about how
the Eliquis would prevent that.

815
00:29:13.752 --> 00:29:16.380
I know.

816
00:29:16.463 --> 00:29:18.757
Well. I finally took
your advice.

817
00:29:18.840 --> 00:29:21.218
I got out of the house.
and I joined

818
00:29:21.301 --> 00:29:23.136
the Frick Park
Lawn Bowling Club.

819
00:29:23.220 --> 00:29:24.429
Wonderful.

820
00:29:24.513 --> 00:29:25.555
Yeah.

821
00:29:25.639 --> 00:29:27.391
I mean. you're right. you know?

822
00:29:27.474 --> 00:29:29.434
We all need a community.

823
00:29:33.480 --> 00:29:34.856
You're gonna do what?

824
00:29:34.940 --> 00:29:36.525
In order to fix your tongue.

825
00:29:36.608 --> 00:29:39.069
we need to move it forward
to access the laceration.

826
00:29:39.152 --> 00:29:40.696
You're just gonna feel
some pulling. OK?

827
00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:44.074
I guess so.

828
00:29:44.157 --> 00:29:46.785
Go for it.

829
00:29:46.868 --> 00:29:48.161
What size suture is that?

830
00:29:48.245 --> 00:29:51.957
O-silk. the biggest one
we got.

831
00:29:52.040 --> 00:29:54.918
As soon as I cut the needle.
you're on traction. Joy.

832
00:30:03.719 --> 00:30:05.178
Oh.

833
00:30:05.262 --> 00:30:07.389
That is pretty deep.

834
00:30:07.472 --> 00:30:08.974
And now we can
numb up the cut.

835
00:30:09.057 --> 00:30:10.309
It's best to start with--

836
00:30:10.392 --> 00:30:11.727
Proximal side first
so she doesn't

837
00:30:11.810 --> 00:30:14.938
feel the distal injection.

838
00:30:15.022 --> 00:30:15.939
Give it ten minutes.

839
00:30:16.023 --> 00:30:17.524
I'll be back for the repair.

840
00:30:21.737 --> 00:30:23.572
I got a rape kit
sitting here for two weeks

841
00:30:23.655 --> 00:30:26.074
that was supposed to be
picked up within 72 hours.

842
00:30:26.158 --> 00:30:27.117
I don't care!

843
00:30:27.200 --> 00:30:29.161
Get someone over here now! No.

844
00:30:29.244 --> 00:30:30.662
You expect us
to treat your officers

845
00:30:30.746 --> 00:30:32.289
as soon as they come in.

846
00:30:32.372 --> 00:30:34.124
you get a detective
to pick these kits up ASAP.

847
00:30:34.207 --> 00:30:35.125
I gotta go.

848
00:30:35.208 --> 00:30:36.710
- Dana--
- Hey. Dana.

849
00:30:36.793 --> 00:30:37.878
South 19 got their head CT
before we went down.

850
00:30:37.961 --> 00:30:39.212
No results yet.

851
00:30:39.296 --> 00:30:40.380
All right.
I'll send a reminder.

852
00:30:40.464 --> 00:30:41.381
- Hey. Dana.
- Dana.

853
00:30:41.465 --> 00:30:42.841
Hang on.

854
00:30:43.884 --> 00:30:45.552
What's up?

855
00:30:45.635 --> 00:30:47.512
We put in an order
for more pain meds for Roxie.

856
00:30:47.596 --> 00:30:49.598
All right. so put it
in the nursing racks.

857
00:30:49.681 --> 00:30:52.225
Oh. I did. a long time ago.

858
00:30:52.309 --> 00:30:54.102
All right.
I'll bump it to the front.

859
00:30:54.186 --> 00:30:55.645
Thank you.

860
00:30:55.729 --> 00:30:57.356
Uh. what's that noise?

861
00:30:57.439 --> 00:30:58.440
UFO landed.

862
00:30:58.523 --> 00:30:59.441
Aliens are invading.

863
00:30:59.524 --> 00:31:00.942
Hey. Dana.

864
00:31:01.026 --> 00:31:02.819
Chem 7's not back
on Trauma 2 yet.

865
00:31:02.903 --> 00:31:05.113
Let me see the chart.

866
00:31:05.197 --> 00:31:06.656
Oh. Jesus.

867
00:31:06.740 --> 00:31:08.200
I bet your Chem 7 rec
went to Radiology.

868
00:31:08.283 --> 00:31:10.035
Larry. Antoine.

869
00:31:10.118 --> 00:31:12.537
You put labs and chest X-ray
on the same downtime form.

870
00:31:12.621 --> 00:31:14.831
You need two slips--one
for labs. one for radiology.

871
00:31:14.915 --> 00:31:16.500
- Got it.
- Won't happen again.

872
00:31:16.583 --> 00:31:17.626
I'll run it down myself.

873
00:31:17.709 --> 00:31:19.336
Use the iStat at bedside.

874
00:31:19.419 --> 00:31:20.754
They won't take him to CT
without a creatinine.

875
00:31:20.837 --> 00:31:21.963
Oh. perfect.

876
00:31:22.047 --> 00:31:23.090
Nice to have you back.

877
00:31:23.173 --> 00:31:24.383
Thrilled to be here.

878
00:31:24.466 --> 00:31:25.509
You trying to text?

879
00:31:25.592 --> 00:31:27.052
I am just composing.

880
00:31:27.135 --> 00:31:28.595
I'm gonna send it from the bay.

881
00:31:28.678 --> 00:31:30.847
My mechanic friend. Duke.
never showed up.

882
00:31:30.931 --> 00:31:32.391
I thought he was
coming in this morning.

883
00:31:32.474 --> 00:31:33.600
That was the plan.

884
00:31:33.683 --> 00:31:35.894
I guess he got busy.

885
00:31:35.977 --> 00:31:37.104
What if he's a no-show?

886
00:31:37.187 --> 00:31:38.730
Tell me what he needs.

887
00:31:38.814 --> 00:31:39.815
I'll pass it on
to the night shift.

888
00:31:39.898 --> 00:31:40.816
That won't be necessary.

889
00:31:43.652 --> 00:31:45.404
Oh. Princess.

890
00:31:45.487 --> 00:31:46.488
Ask and you shall receive.

891
00:31:46.571 --> 00:31:47.614
Normal head CT.

892
00:31:47.697 --> 00:31:49.991
Thanks.
I'll get him discharged.

893
00:31:50.075 --> 00:31:51.827
How's your day going?

894
00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:54.329
I think I'm getting
writer's cramp.

895
00:31:54.413 --> 00:31:55.664
You with the big guy?

896
00:31:55.747 --> 00:31:57.916
Yeah. It's sad.

897
00:31:57.999 --> 00:32:01.837
Bad car accident. multiple
operations. tons of stress.

898
00:32:03.922 --> 00:32:05.715
Lidocaine shot
to a sensitive area.

899
00:32:05.799 --> 00:32:07.467
I got a binge-drinking
party girl with a tongue lac.

900
00:32:07.551 --> 00:32:08.802
Mm.

901
00:32:08.885 --> 00:32:10.053
Sounds like
she needs some help.

902
00:32:10.137 --> 00:32:12.764
In more ways than one.

903
00:32:12.848 --> 00:32:16.476
How's. uh--how's
your first shift back going?

904
00:32:16.560 --> 00:32:18.687
One day at a time.

905
00:32:18.770 --> 00:32:20.272
First year sober
is the hardest.

906
00:32:20.355 --> 00:32:21.523
That's what
they keep telling me.

907
00:32:21.606 --> 00:32:24.192
I'm nine years and counting.

908
00:32:26.653 --> 00:32:28.155
Oh.

909
00:32:28.238 --> 00:32:31.700
Special delivery for my guy.

910
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:33.660
If you. um--if you
need anything. call me.

911
00:32:33.743 --> 00:32:35.328
Thanks.

912
00:32:41.334 --> 00:32:42.878
Where are you going?

913
00:32:42.961 --> 00:32:44.254
Blisters in North 3.

914
00:32:44.337 --> 00:32:45.755
That's where I'm going.

915
00:32:45.839 --> 00:32:47.632
Did you sign up
for the patient?

916
00:32:47.716 --> 00:32:49.426
I pulled the chart
from the rack.

917
00:32:49.509 --> 00:32:51.178
You're supposed to sign up
on the dry-erase board.

918
00:32:51.261 --> 00:32:53.054
You're supposed to have
a clipboard for the patient.

919
00:32:53.138 --> 00:32:54.848
I thought
the nurses had that.

920
00:32:54.931 --> 00:32:56.475
Whatever.

921
00:32:56.558 --> 00:32:57.601
Hi.

922
00:32:57.684 --> 00:32:59.019
I'm Student Doctor Ogilvie.

923
00:32:59.102 --> 00:33:01.229
And this is--wow.

924
00:33:01.313 --> 00:33:02.689
That is some rash.

925
00:33:02.772 --> 00:33:05.567
- Yeah. Tell me about it.
- Student Doctor Javadi.

926
00:33:05.650 --> 00:33:07.777
- When did this start?
- Last night.

927
00:33:07.861 --> 00:33:09.321
And have you been
on any hikes recently

928
00:33:09.404 --> 00:33:10.447
around poison ivy?

929
00:33:10.530 --> 00:33:12.365
Nope. Haven't left the house.

930
00:33:12.449 --> 00:33:15.368
What about new medications.
lotions. soaps.

931
00:33:15.452 --> 00:33:16.369
detergents. even?

932
00:33:16.453 --> 00:33:17.662
I don't take medicine.

933
00:33:17.746 --> 00:33:19.331
Nothing new with all
that other stuff.

934
00:33:19.414 --> 00:33:20.415
Uh-huh.
And where did this start?

935
00:33:20.499 --> 00:33:21.833
Everywhere. all at once.

936
00:33:21.917 --> 00:33:25.170
Just a lot of pain.
really itchy.

937
00:33:25.253 --> 00:33:26.880
What is it?

938
00:33:26.963 --> 00:33:28.381
I'm not sure yet.

939
00:33:28.465 --> 00:33:31.134
Um. be back in a second.

940
00:33:31.218 --> 00:33:32.761
Can't--will you--

941
00:33:37.015 --> 00:33:38.975
What are you thinking?

942
00:33:39.059 --> 00:33:40.060
I have no idea.

943
00:33:40.143 --> 00:33:41.311
Agreed.

944
00:33:43.188 --> 00:33:44.689
Bullous pemphigoid?

945
00:33:44.773 --> 00:33:46.399
Autoimmune severe pruritis?

946
00:33:46.483 --> 00:33:48.026
Yeah. but not as deadly
as pemphigus vulgaris.

947
00:33:48.109 --> 00:33:50.028
Untreated. the death rate
is over 90%.

948
00:33:50.111 --> 00:33:51.446
We need to check
for pustules.

949
00:33:51.530 --> 00:33:52.572
mucous membrane involvement--

950
00:33:52.656 --> 00:33:54.032
And the Nikolsky sign.

951
00:33:56.535 --> 00:33:57.911
Here you go.

952
00:33:59.412 --> 00:34:00.413
What?

953
00:34:00.497 --> 00:34:02.040
For your progress note.

954
00:34:03.416 --> 00:34:06.336
Did I hear
we're making progress?

955
00:34:06.419 --> 00:34:08.630
Oh. um.
it's just what we call it

956
00:34:08.713 --> 00:34:11.800
when we write down things
to describe a clinical course.

957
00:34:13.342 --> 00:34:14.302
Any changes?

958
00:34:15.387 --> 00:34:16.596
Not so far.

959
00:34:16.679 --> 00:34:18.974
It's time for the next
neuro check.

960
00:34:19.056 --> 00:34:21.268
Excuse me. Dr. King.
do you have a minute?

961
00:34:21.351 --> 00:34:22.851
Um. no.

962
00:34:22.936 --> 00:34:24.646
I'm observing
a patient right now.

963
00:34:24.728 --> 00:34:27.065
60 seconds tops.

964
00:34:28.483 --> 00:34:29.775
I'll check pupils.

965
00:34:29.859 --> 00:34:31.402
We're good here.

966
00:34:37.033 --> 00:34:38.909
Hey.

967
00:34:38.994 --> 00:34:41.246
I just finished
my deposition.

968
00:34:41.329 --> 00:34:43.706
Oh. should I go up now?

969
00:34:43.790 --> 00:34:45.417
Yeah.
Just wait until you get a call.

970
00:34:45.500 --> 00:34:46.793
OK.

971
00:34:46.876 --> 00:34:48.253
Well. I'd ask how it went.

972
00:34:48.335 --> 00:34:50.297
but we're not supposed
to discuss the case.

973
00:34:50.380 --> 00:34:51.797
This isn't a discussion.

974
00:34:51.880 --> 00:34:55.051
It's a monologue.
so shut up and listen.

975
00:34:55.135 --> 00:34:57.262
The malpractice case
is frivolous.

976
00:34:57.345 --> 00:34:58.805
The mother
of the measles kid claims

977
00:34:58.888 --> 00:35:00.223
we caused intellectual decline

978
00:35:00.307 --> 00:35:02.309
by performing a spinal tap.

979
00:35:02.392 --> 00:35:05.520
But the tap was perfect
with no complications.

980
00:35:05.604 --> 00:35:07.272
Her son presented
with altered mental status

981
00:35:07.355 --> 00:35:10.734
due to low oxygen
from measles pneumonia.

982
00:35:10.817 --> 00:35:13.194
Any change in intellect was
due to hypoxic brain injury.

983
00:35:13.278 --> 00:35:16.865
It had nothing to do
with your spinal tap.

984
00:35:16.948 --> 00:35:18.575
End of monologue.

985
00:35:18.658 --> 00:35:21.328
We never discussed the case.

986
00:35:21.411 --> 00:35:23.663
I gotta get some sleep.

987
00:35:23.747 --> 00:35:27.000
Thanks. I guess.

988
00:35:28.668 --> 00:35:30.879
OK. are you ready
to lay down?

989
00:35:30.962 --> 00:35:31.880
I got your head.

990
00:35:31.963 --> 00:35:33.089
Nice and slow.

991
00:35:33.173 --> 00:35:35.300
One. two. three.

992
00:35:36.718 --> 00:35:37.636
OK.

993
00:35:37.719 --> 00:35:38.803
How's that feel?

994
00:35:41.723 --> 00:35:42.849
Lifting up now.

995
00:35:52.859 --> 00:35:54.486
Keep going.

996
00:35:57.113 --> 00:36:00.367
And...that ought to do it
right about there.

997
00:36:02.118 --> 00:36:03.870
215?

998
00:36:03.953 --> 00:36:05.872
Oh. that's in kilos.

999
00:36:08.208 --> 00:36:09.793
OK. team.

1000
00:36:15.423 --> 00:36:17.092
It's not that much over 450.

1001
00:36:17.175 --> 00:36:19.886
No. we can't risk breaking
our CT on a holiday weekend.

1002
00:36:19.969 --> 00:36:22.013
Would the medics take him
while he's intubated?

1003
00:36:22.097 --> 00:36:24.391
If I go along for the ride.
I could still get a nap in

1004
00:36:24.474 --> 00:36:26.017
before my night shift.

1005
00:36:30.021 --> 00:36:32.899
474.

1006
00:36:32.982 --> 00:36:34.776
Our CT can't handle
your weight.

1007
00:36:34.859 --> 00:36:38.154
but we're gonna take you over
to Presbyterian Hospital.

1008
00:36:38.238 --> 00:36:40.073
Road trip.

1009
00:36:40.156 --> 00:36:42.450
I'll keep you company
the whole time.

1010
00:36:44.994 --> 00:36:46.996
Sorry for all this trouble.

1011
00:36:47.080 --> 00:36:48.206
It's OK.

1012
00:36:48.289 --> 00:36:49.708
This is what we do.

1013
00:36:55.213 --> 00:36:56.715
So sub Q starts deep.

1014
00:36:56.798 --> 00:36:57.841
You want to bury the knot.

1015
00:36:57.924 --> 00:36:59.384
Yeah. I've done these before.

1016
00:36:59.467 --> 00:37:01.678
Joy. how do we cut the ends?

1017
00:37:01.761 --> 00:37:03.221
Short.
Slide to the knot.

1018
00:37:03.304 --> 00:37:04.222
Turn 45 degrees.

1019
00:37:04.305 --> 00:37:06.349
Excellent.

1020
00:37:06.433 --> 00:37:08.184
Um. Dr. Langdon.
we have a case.

1021
00:37:08.268 --> 00:37:09.185
It'll have to wait.

1022
00:37:09.269 --> 00:37:10.311
It could be urgent.

1023
00:37:10.395 --> 00:37:14.149
Find Robby or Al-Hashimi.

1024
00:37:14.232 --> 00:37:16.484
This girl is wasted.

1025
00:37:16.568 --> 00:37:18.528
Drunk as a skunk.

1026
00:37:18.611 --> 00:37:20.280
Should we check
her blood alcohol level?

1027
00:37:20.363 --> 00:37:21.906
No. it won't change
what we do.

1028
00:37:21.990 --> 00:37:23.491
She can go home
when she has a steady gait.

1029
00:37:23.575 --> 00:37:25.660
I already sent one off.

1030
00:37:25.744 --> 00:37:28.329
Joy. do you want to guess
her blood alcohol?

1031
00:37:28.413 --> 00:37:29.831
Why would I want to do that?

1032
00:37:29.914 --> 00:37:31.958
I don't know.
'Cause it's fun.

1033
00:37:37.964 --> 00:37:39.549
When will you have a bed?

1034
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:41.384
I'm not sure she needs a bed.

1035
00:37:41.468 --> 00:37:43.178
She's a febrile infant.

1036
00:37:43.261 --> 00:37:45.138
Who is clearly over a month
old and looks amazing.

1037
00:37:45.221 --> 00:37:47.098
Every marker is normal.
She has a cold virus.

1038
00:37:47.182 --> 00:37:48.850
Infants with rhinovirus
can still have

1039
00:37:48.933 --> 00:37:50.268
a serious bacterial infection.

1040
00:37:50.351 --> 00:37:51.770
Not this one.

1041
00:37:51.853 --> 00:37:53.396
We send kids like this home
all the time.

1042
00:37:53.480 --> 00:37:56.441
Except this one doesn't have
a home or a parent.

1043
00:37:57.817 --> 00:37:59.277
All right.

1044
00:37:59.360 --> 00:38:01.029
I can't put a kid
with a virus in the nursery.

1045
00:38:01.112 --> 00:38:03.281
and I can't waste a private
room on a healthy baby.

1046
00:38:03.364 --> 00:38:04.699
Then what do you propose?

1047
00:38:04.783 --> 00:38:06.659
CYF can place her
in emergency foster care

1048
00:38:06.743 --> 00:38:08.203
by tomorrow morning.

1049
00:38:08.286 --> 00:38:10.413
You want to leave her
down here overnight?

1050
00:38:10.497 --> 00:38:12.791
Seems to be the standard
of care these days.

1051
00:38:12.874 --> 00:38:14.125
Have your attending
give me a call.

1052
00:38:14.209 --> 00:38:15.168
Will do.

1053
00:38:15.251 --> 00:38:16.503
I can't believe this.

1054
00:38:16.586 --> 00:38:18.296
Let CYF know
it's very urgent.

1055
00:38:18.379 --> 00:38:19.798
Got it.

1056
00:38:19.881 --> 00:38:22.342
This is turning
into quite the day.

1057
00:38:22.425 --> 00:38:24.260
You know. I've been thinking

1058
00:38:24.344 --> 00:38:25.804
about applying
for a fellowship.

1059
00:38:25.887 --> 00:38:27.764
I thought you had a job
lined up in New Jersey.

1060
00:38:27.847 --> 00:38:29.891
I did. to be close to my mom.

1061
00:38:29.974 --> 00:38:33.436
But she sold her house
to travel the world

1062
00:38:33.520 --> 00:38:35.438
with her new boyfriend.

1063
00:38:35.522 --> 00:38:37.273
So what's the point
of New Jersey?

1064
00:38:37.357 --> 00:38:38.691
Yeah. good question.

1065
00:38:38.775 --> 00:38:40.318
Which fellowship?

1066
00:38:40.401 --> 00:38:44.030
I've narrowed it down
to ultrasound. toxicology.

1067
00:38:44.113 --> 00:38:47.283
and sports medicine.

1068
00:38:47.367 --> 00:38:48.660
Those are
very disparate fields

1069
00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:50.161
leading to very
different careers.

1070
00:38:50.245 --> 00:38:51.329
I know.

1071
00:38:51.412 --> 00:38:53.414
I'm a little undecided.

1072
00:38:53.498 --> 00:38:55.041
Do you have
research experience?

1073
00:38:55.124 --> 00:38:57.627
I was a part of a study
on racial disparities

1074
00:38:57.710 --> 00:38:59.504
in health care
until the White House

1075
00:38:59.587 --> 00:39:01.047
cut the funding last year.

1076
00:39:01.130 --> 00:39:03.466
Yeah. You are not alone.

1077
00:39:03.550 --> 00:39:06.386
Have you considered
a geriatrics fellowship?

1078
00:39:06.469 --> 00:39:08.304
I have not.

1079
00:39:08.388 --> 00:39:10.431
I've seen your skills
with the elderly.

1080
00:39:10.515 --> 00:39:12.559
and there are
a lot of openings.

1081
00:39:12.642 --> 00:39:14.394
It might be your best shot.

1082
00:39:14.477 --> 00:39:17.230
Think about it.

1083
00:39:17.313 --> 00:39:18.231
Last stitch.

1084
00:39:18.314 --> 00:39:19.315
You want me to cut?

1085
00:39:19.399 --> 00:39:20.859
I got it.

1086
00:39:22.569 --> 00:39:23.820
It looks good.

1087
00:39:23.903 --> 00:39:25.905
OK.
Let's pull the traction suture.

1088
00:39:25.989 --> 00:39:27.365
With pleasure.

1089
00:39:29.325 --> 00:39:31.369
OK. Jackie.

1090
00:39:31.452 --> 00:39:32.787
- Jackie.
- Stop it.

1091
00:39:32.871 --> 00:39:33.788
Stop.

1092
00:39:33.872 --> 00:39:35.081
All done.

1093
00:39:35.164 --> 00:39:36.666
All done with what?

1094
00:39:36.749 --> 00:39:38.334
Sewing up your tongue.

1095
00:39:38.418 --> 00:39:40.044
What happened to my tongue?

1096
00:39:40.128 --> 00:39:41.254
You bit it.

1097
00:39:41.337 --> 00:39:42.255
Ha.

1098
00:39:42.338 --> 00:39:43.923
No. I didn't.

1099
00:39:44.007 --> 00:39:45.758
That is called a blackout.

1100
00:39:45.842 --> 00:39:47.594
How much did you drink?

1101
00:39:47.677 --> 00:39:49.846
A couple Bloody Marys.

1102
00:39:49.929 --> 00:39:51.055
Only a couple?

1103
00:39:51.139 --> 00:39:53.224
I don't know. Maybe more.

1104
00:39:53.308 --> 00:39:55.935
It's a holiday. a pub crawl.

1105
00:39:56.019 --> 00:39:58.646
Do you usually have
a couple cocktails every day?

1106
00:39:58.730 --> 00:39:59.898
Only on weekends.

1107
00:39:59.981 --> 00:40:01.232
How about during the week?

1108
00:40:01.316 --> 00:40:02.650
Nothing much.

1109
00:40:02.734 --> 00:40:07.655
Just wine with dinner
or a few beers.

1110
00:40:07.739 --> 00:40:10.825
Maybe we should
recommend rehab?

1111
00:40:10.909 --> 00:40:11.910
Yeah.

1112
00:40:11.993 --> 00:40:13.411
We could try.

1113
00:40:17.999 --> 00:40:20.376
Ready to roll.

1114
00:40:20.460 --> 00:40:22.003
How are you feeling?

1115
00:40:22.086 --> 00:40:23.379
My pain is a two.

1116
00:40:23.463 --> 00:40:24.964
We got meds if you need them.

1117
00:40:25.048 --> 00:40:26.507
Scan will be quicker
than the ride to Presby.

1118
00:40:26.591 --> 00:40:27.884
We'll keep trying
to reach your sister.

1119
00:40:27.967 --> 00:40:29.510
- You guys are the best.
- See you later.

1120
00:40:29.594 --> 00:40:31.304
Can I put a new patient
in T1?

1121
00:40:31.387 --> 00:40:33.681
Uh. no. I kind of want
to leave one trauma room open.

1122
00:40:33.765 --> 00:40:37.310
Why don't you double up
the north if you have to?

1123
00:40:37.393 --> 00:40:40.229
Mr. Digby?

1124
00:40:40.313 --> 00:40:42.106
- It's just Digby.
- Right.

1125
00:40:42.190 --> 00:40:44.651
We've been looking all over.
Where you been?

1126
00:40:44.734 --> 00:40:46.194
With Louie.

1127
00:40:46.277 --> 00:40:47.695
You've been in there
for an hour?

1128
00:40:47.779 --> 00:40:49.739
He was my friend.

1129
00:40:49.822 --> 00:40:51.658
- I had a lot to say.
- Hmm.

1130
00:40:51.741 --> 00:40:54.035
Well. let's get you
back to your bed.

1131
00:40:56.120 --> 00:40:57.914
Louie got his wings.

1132
00:40:57.997 --> 00:40:59.832
- Dr. Robby.
- Dr. Robby.

1133
00:40:59.916 --> 00:41:01.417
We picked up
a patient together.

1134
00:41:01.501 --> 00:41:02.835
Teamwork!

1135
00:41:02.919 --> 00:41:04.379
It's a concerning
bullous rash.

1136
00:41:04.462 --> 00:41:05.964
We might need a biopsy
for pemphigus vulgaris.

1137
00:41:06.047 --> 00:41:07.423
It's phytophotodermatitis.

1138
00:41:07.507 --> 00:41:09.175
- What?
- I asked.

1139
00:41:09.258 --> 00:41:11.302
He was making three gallons
of margaritas for a party.

1140
00:41:11.386 --> 00:41:13.554
squeezing fresh limes
out in the sun.

1141
00:41:13.638 --> 00:41:14.973
Let's go take a peek.

1142
00:41:15.056 --> 00:41:16.891
I don't need to see it again.

1143
00:41:19.435 --> 00:41:20.812
How's it going out there?

1144
00:41:20.895 --> 00:41:22.397
Standing room only.

1145
00:41:22.480 --> 00:41:23.815
If I call the fire department.
will they clear

1146
00:41:23.898 --> 00:41:25.108
- that waiting room?
- I wish.

1147
00:41:25.191 --> 00:41:26.234
What's up?

1148
00:41:26.317 --> 00:41:28.277
12 patients need med refills.

1149
00:41:28.361 --> 00:41:29.862
Shouldn't they see
their doctors?

1150
00:41:29.946 --> 00:41:31.614
With the Medicaid cuts.
we are their doctor.

1151
00:41:31.698 --> 00:41:33.324
No. I can't e-prescribe
to their pharmacies.

1152
00:41:33.408 --> 00:41:35.034
So get out your pen.
Go old school.

1153
00:41:35.118 --> 00:41:37.370
Dana. on what?

1154
00:41:37.453 --> 00:41:39.831
Nordt. you got
the security pads?

1155
00:41:39.914 --> 00:41:41.124
Sure do.

1156
00:41:41.207 --> 00:41:42.917
Just need a patient sticker.

1157
00:41:43.001 --> 00:41:45.294
- Any other questions?
- Yeah.

1158
00:41:45.378 --> 00:41:47.755
What would have happened
if you weren't here today?

1159
00:41:48.965 --> 00:41:50.717
You'd all be curled up
in the fetal position.

1160
00:41:50.800 --> 00:41:53.052
crying like babies.

1161
00:41:53.136 --> 00:41:54.679
Were you wearing flip-flops?

1162
00:41:54.762 --> 00:41:56.014
I was.

1163
00:41:56.097 --> 00:41:57.932
- What is it?
- Phytophotodermatitis.

1164
00:41:58.016 --> 00:42:00.143
Otherwise known
as margarita burn.

1165
00:42:00.226 --> 00:42:01.686
For some people.
limes plus sunshine

1166
00:42:01.769 --> 00:42:03.021
can cause a horrible rash.

1167
00:42:03.104 --> 00:42:05.148
This is all because of limes?

1168
00:42:05.231 --> 00:42:07.984
Have you ever squeezed limes
outside in the sun before?

1169
00:42:08.067 --> 00:42:09.652
I don't think so.

1170
00:42:09.736 --> 00:42:12.113
You will feel better
after a day of steroid pills.

1171
00:42:12.196 --> 00:42:14.032
But once these heal.
you gotta wear sunscreen.

1172
00:42:14.115 --> 00:42:16.159
Because these blisters
can turn into dark scars

1173
00:42:16.242 --> 00:42:17.410
and stay a while if you don't.

1174
00:42:19.120 --> 00:42:22.373
I'll be right back with
your aftercare instructions.

1175
00:42:22.457 --> 00:42:24.333
- Hey. Robby.
- Yep.

1176
00:42:24.417 --> 00:42:26.502
My. uh--
my hospice patient Roxie

1177
00:42:26.586 --> 00:42:28.421
is still in a ton of pain.

1178
00:42:28.504 --> 00:42:29.714
Where are we
with the morphine?

1179
00:42:29.797 --> 00:42:31.674
10 milligrams an hour.

1180
00:42:31.758 --> 00:42:34.218
OK. you can bolus another 2
and go up to 12.

1181
00:42:34.302 --> 00:42:35.595
I will let Princess know.

1182
00:42:35.678 --> 00:42:36.971
12 an hour is a lot.

1183
00:42:37.055 --> 00:42:38.431
Yeah. on top
of the MS Contin.

1184
00:42:38.514 --> 00:42:41.392
she could stop breathing.

1185
00:42:41.476 --> 00:42:44.729
Are you familiar with
the doctrine of double effect?

1186
00:42:44.812 --> 00:42:46.814
- Not really.
- No.

1187
00:42:46.898 --> 00:42:49.317
It is an ethical principle
in palliative care.

1188
00:42:49.400 --> 00:42:51.027
We treat pain.

1189
00:42:51.110 --> 00:42:52.987
And if. in doing so.
there's a negative side effect.

1190
00:42:53.071 --> 00:42:54.614
we accept it.

1191
00:42:54.697 --> 00:42:57.450
Even if the negative
side effect is death?

1192
00:42:57.533 --> 00:43:00.161
In some cases.
that could be the best outcome.

1193
00:43:06.000 --> 00:43:07.376
Maybe the nurse has it.

1194
00:43:07.460 --> 00:43:10.088
Emma. Emma. where does--

1195
00:43:10.171 --> 00:43:11.839
Maybe the fax
ran out of paper?

1196
00:43:11.923 --> 00:43:14.550
No. there is enough paper.
I don't know what's wrong.

1197
00:43:14.634 --> 00:43:16.052
- Could be in another room.
- We should call IT.

1198
00:43:16.135 --> 00:43:18.054
You want me to check
every room?

1199
00:43:18.137 --> 00:43:19.639
How are we gonna
get through this mess?

1200
00:43:19.722 --> 00:43:22.600
I was about to ask you.

1201
00:43:22.683 --> 00:43:24.143
Ask the pharmacist.

1202
00:43:24.227 --> 00:43:25.728
She can't leave the PDS.

1203
00:43:25.812 --> 00:43:27.522
Nothing's getting done here.
